sandbox play loops
leaderboards
menus (unless accessibility mode is on)
3. Accessibility Notes (Reddit / App Review Ready)
You can publish this almost verbatim.
Accessibility Statement â€“ FlexWord
FlexWord is designed to be accessible, respectful, and playable by a wide range of users.
Visual Accessibility
Color is not the only feedback mechanism
Textual explanations accompany results
High-contrast UI themes supported
No reliance on color alone for correctness
Audio Accessibility
Sound effects are optional and off by default
Subtle audio cues are available for:
confirmations
successes
result summaries
Audio cues supplement â€” never replace â€” visual feedback
Screen Reader Support
FlexWord supports screen readers by:
Announcing guess results in plain language
Reading contract outcomes and payouts
Avoiding purely visual-only game states
Example:
â€œTwo letters correct. One misplaced. Three incorrect.â€
Cognitive Accessibility
One ranked play per day (no grind pressure)
Sandbox mode for stress-free play
No timed actions
No audio urgency cues
Player Control
All sound features can be disabled
Gameplay remains fully functional without audio
No hidden audio-dependent mechanics
Accessibility Philosophy (Summary)
FlexWord prioritizes:
clarity over spectacle
fairness over stimulation
agency over compulsion
Accessibility is treated as part of good game design, not an add-on.